<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">MADMAN</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ok i am a new lvl 52 cleric my friend has left eq and now 52 cleric is all mine! so basicaly i need to know what spell should i do he says he has all spells up to his lvl, also any quests i can do becuase i will be transfering him to a differnt server so he will be naked. i cant aford anything for him really beacuse in was hacked recntly and have nothing. also any tips techniques would be great. thanks all latez!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Arturo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hit the blue button...<P>------------------<BR>Arturo Fuente<BR>Venerable Priest of Mithaniel Marr<BR>Circle of Legends<BR>Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You want some REAL advice? <P>Lose the account. Seriously. If it got hacked once, it can happen again, and you don't know how many people your "friend" gave his info out to.<P>ALSO, if you read the Character transfer policy, it specifically says all info on the account MUST be the original owner.<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>If you attempt to transfer characters in violation of these guidelines and restrictions, any laws, the EUASL or the Rules of Conduct(for instance, attempting to transfer characters from another person's account or to or from an account purchased by or for you or <B>given to you where you are not the original registered user of that account</B>), the characters will not be moved, your request will not be processed or approved and your account(s) will be subject to review and appropriate disciplinary action taken.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Trying to transfer a charater that is on an account that wasn't originally registered to you WILL throw up some red flags, and VI can (and most likely WILL) ban that account and all your other accounts as well.<P>You would be better off just spending the $40 for a new account and powerleveling a cleric up. It's not hard, and you can get to 50 in about 2 weeks or less.<P>For more info on character moves, use this link:<BR>https://store.station.sony.com/eq_char_moves/</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Skwar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I mean no offense by this.. but I would just start over.<P>The learning curve to pick up a Cleric 50+ for the first time and try to fit in where the characters need you most is <B>steep</B> at best!  Maybe I am speaking from personal experience here, but even at my age I'm schooled regularly by my elders with things I could be doing to make Clerics more efficient.  Unless you have someone to coach you (<B>a lot</B>).. I'd start you a new one and learn the class.<P>BUT, if you wish to stick with it, you do have a long road to get some gear for your age, if yer gonna be nekkid.  I wish you the best of luck!<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=57051" TARGET=_blank>Skwar Rewt</A><BR>Proud Cleric & Officer of Clan Chaos<BR>43rd Half-Pint Medic of Xev</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Also, I agree. The learning curve is steep, and to just pick up and go with a 52 cleric isn't going to be easy. I chose not to go with this argument, because I am SURE you will try to defend your reasoning in any number of ways. (Most of which are just alot of hot air, but I don't feel like shooting them down.)<P>Simply put, taking over this account is going to be more hassle than it's worth. If you DO choose to continue with this route, I wish you luck. It would be a shame to pay the 50$ to move then get the account banned (or worse, ALL your accounts banned). Likewise, it would be a shame to get the character successfully moved, then equip him, then get hacked again OR have the original owner take the account back by claiming YOU hacked HIM (this has happened before). It's your $50, though. I think it would be better spent by buying a new account (the trilogy is what? $30?). But that's just my opinion.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Napper</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You wont get sympathy or assistance from clerics who made their toons from scratch and take pride in them because of that.<P>Napper</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Emmhim</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hello MadMan<P>I agree with everybody here that you have so much to learn that you will be a danger for your group for a long time.<P>But I don't think that will make you cancel the cleric, so to make you less of a danger, I will give you a few advices:<BR>- Read through the descriptions of every spell, technique, etc. - everything you can find. At least here on EQcleric and on EQCasters ( <A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/" TARGET=_blank>http://eq.castersrealm.com/</A>  ). You need to learn things like assist-healing, proper buffing, etc., and EQCleric is a goldmine of information for you.<P>After that:<BR>- Go to a newbie area and start powerlevelling somebody. This will give you some better feeling of what the spells do and how long time they take to cast. You will also learn that some of your best buffs will not work on lowbies :-)<BR>- Move up to a mid level area (lvl 25-40) and powerlevel some more. Could e.g. try first LoIO, and them move to OT.<BR>- Try some soloing of light blue stuff<BR>- Do everything else you can think of that will make you learn the spells, but not bring other people in danger.<P>At the same time, you can earn some money e.g. from ressing people, and buy some equipment to start with.<P>When you feel confident that you got the basics, go find a tank on your own level. Tell that you are a 'newbie' and if that does not scare the tank away, go somewhere and kill things. At your level, a place like the Giant Fort in BW could be good - or the spectrals in TT - or some other low risk place with easy single pulling.<BR>After some low-risk duoing, you can e.g. try a group right inside KC, etc.<BR>Build up your healing and buffing skills slowly that way.<P>Be careful when you enter a new area. You do not know which factions your cleric has screqed up (e.g. from hunting in Plane of Growth), so always approach a town carefully - conning the guards and citizens.<P>Last advice: For the first many days you group with people - be honest. Tell people that you are less than 100% skilled with the cleric. Their lives depend on you, so they deserve to know the situation. It will probably also make them pull a little more slowly, so you will loose less people.<P>Greetings<BR>Emmhim ManaLow<BR>Lvl 59 Templar<BR>A Mighty Dane from the Antonius Bayle server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">DurokH</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Delete him - or at least put him in cold storage for a long time.  If you have never played, EQ, enjoy the newbie game - you can only do that once and don't miss the opportunity.<P>Durok<BR>Vicar of Brell<BR></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
